Class PegSolitaireSolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • PegSolitaireSolver
  • public final class PegSolitaireSolver
extends java.lang.Object
    This PegSolitaireSolver program is a program to solve peg solitaire board games. Uses DFS = depth for search for the backtracking and a backward pruning technique to only hold needed game states as it goes.
    Since:
    2020-09-23
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nate

      • solvedboard

        private static boolean solvedboard​(int[][] pegbrd)
        Parameters:
        pegbrd - the peg board
        Returns:
        true for now but can be customized with more specific requirements. Like the last peg has to be in
 the middle peg hole for it to be a solution... currently a solution to peg solitaire is any move sequence that ends with only one peg on the 
 board. So this method is just a stub function that always returns true add your code to it to customize requirements / constraints for a board to be solved.
 RIGHT NOW ITS NOT USED AS A SOLUTION IS REACH WHEN ONLY ONE PEG IS LEFT DOESNT MATTER WHERE IT IS LEFT.
 YOU MAY FEEL DIFFERENTLY ABOUT THIS AND WANT TO CUSTOMIZE IT TO A SPECIFIC PLACE ONBOARD OR OTHER REQUIREMENTS!
